org.tiledreader

Class TiledObjectTemplate

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tiledreader.TiledResource
      • org.tiledreader.TiledObjectTemplate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TiledCustomizable

    public class TiledObjectTemplate
extends TiledResource
implements TiledCustomizable

    A TiledObjectTemplate represents a template from which TiledObjects can borrow their default properties. It corresponds to a <template> tag in a Tiled XML file.

    Author:
    Alex Heyman

      • getPoints

        public final List<Point2D> getPoints()
        Returns an unmodifiable List view of the sequence of vertex (x, y) coordinates of objects with this template, if this template is for a polygon or polyline. Returns an empty unmodifiable List otherwise. The coordinates are relative to the (x, y) positions of objects with this template.

      • getProperties

        public final Map<String,Object> getProperties()
        Description copied from interface: TiledCustomizable
        Returns an unmodifiable Map view of this entity's custom properties. Each key in the Map is the name of a property, and its corresponding value is the value of that property. The type of the value object corresponds to the type of the property: String for a string property, Integer for an int, Float for a float, Boolean for a bool, java.awt.Color for a color, TiledFile for a file, and TiledObject for an object (unless the object property is unset, in which case the value is null).
        Specified by:
        getProperties in interface TiledCustomizable
        Returns:
        This entity's custom properties
